<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-69-0924 </DOCNO><TEXT>The author conducted research in Hiroshima over a six-month period in1962. This article describes his findings by looking at the Hiroshimaexperience as taking place in four stages. The author concludes thatthere was a total breakdown of the social and communal structure - ofthe web of institution and arrangements necessary to the function ofany human group in Hiroshima. However, the existence and interventionof an intact outside world made that social breakdown temporary. Today,there are so many nuclear warheads, the author says there will be nointact outside world to help should they be launched.</TEXT></DOC>